  <body>
    <section name="SchemaCrawler - ant Task Example">
      <subsection name="Description">
        <p>The ant task example demonstrates the use of the
          &lt;schemacrawler&gt; ant macro that comes bundled with
          SchemaCrawler.
        </p>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="How to Run">
        <ol>
          <li>
            Install
            <a href="http://ant.apache.org/">ant,</a>
            and make sure that ant is on your
            path
          </li>
          <li>
            Make sure that
            <span class="code">java</span>
            is on your
            <span class="code">PATH</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            Start the database server by running the
            <span class="code">StartDatabaseServer</span>
            script from the
            distribution directory
          </li>
          <li>
            Run
            <span class="code">ant</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            See the output produced in the
            <span class="code">snapshot.txt</span>
            file
          </li>
        </ol>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="How to Experiment">
        <ol>
          <li>
            Edit
            <span class="code">build.xml</span>
            , and try using different SchemaCrawler commands.
          </li>
          <li>
            Edit
            <span class="code">build.xml</span>
            , and try defining a new database connection, using your favorite
            database and
            driver.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </subsection>
    </section>
  </body>
